			<div id="post_message_279280">
				<blockquote class="postcontent restore">
					Just watch the video titled &quot;Carmack plays Wolfenstein&quot; on youtube. A year ago he was claiming that opensource was good,brilliant, wonderfull - he gave away source to engines, and people porting it to various platforms. So, when he needed iOS port, he simply took existing work by other hacker and modified it a bit.<br />
<br />
Now, knowing that Linux is NOT a monopoly and is not force-preinstalled on 90% of PC, trying to claim that &quot;Linux is different story altogether&quot; is halfarsed attitude at best.<br />
<br />
It is same story, Carmack - you get what you put in. What have you done for Linux development as gaming platform? Any exclusive titles?
				</blockquote>
