				</div>
				<div class="message">Those games will most likely nobody want to play when you have to change the os first.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>I will repeat myself yet again. You get what you put in. You put &quot;don't want to change OS&quot;, you get &quot;can't play game&quot; out. <br />
If you want to play, change OS. If you and other change OS, this will change OS market balance and trigger more income in the area.<br />
<br />
I just hope those &quot;speeches&quot; of JC are not signs of his age. Getting more comfortable, stable, streamlined, simple. Doom 1 + N. That is... :/<br />
But if ID releases no Doom 4 for Linux, I have no problem throwing them into abyss of oblivion. They get what they seed.
